start: ^Good morning. We begin today with a developing story out of northern Maine. State Police say they are continuing the search for two women reported missing earlier this week. The pair were last seen driving into the North Woods late Sunday night.
news_details_1: ^Authorities say the women were traveling along Route 11, a long and isolated highway through dense forest. Investigators believe the vehicle may have turned onto an unmarked logging road after midnight. That area is known for pitch-dark conditions, minimal cell service, and few, if any, passersby.
news_details_2: ^Search crews continue to focus on remote logging roads, abandoned campsites, and forest pull-offs. Police warn that visibility is extremely limited and the rugged terrain makes recovery efforts difficult. No confirmed sightings have been reported since Sunday night.
news_close: ^Authorities are urging anyone who traveled through the area to come forward. The investigation remains ongoing. We’ll bring you more as this develops.
